Goal 13: Climate Action

To strengthen resilience and adaptive capacity to climate related disasters.

Reducing the death rates and the other people who are directly affected due to natural disasters in all the countries.

To identify and ensure that all countries adapt to and implement disaster risk reduction strategies in line with Sendai Framework for Disaster Risk Reduction 2015- 2030.

Integrating climate change measures into policy and planning.

Building knowledge and capacity to meet climate change.

Promote mechanisms to raise capacity for planning and management in least developed countries and small island developing states including focusing on women , youth and local and marginalized communities.

Mobilizing financial support to address the needs of developing countries to adapt to climate change and also investing in low carbon development.

Improving education , raising awareness and human and institutional capacity on climate change mitigation ,adaptation and impact reduction.

Implementing the commitment undertaken by developedcountry parties to the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change to a goal of mobilizing jointly $100 billion annually by 2020 from all sources to address the needs of developing countries in the context of meaningful mitigation actions and transparency on implementation and fully operationalize the Green Climate Fund through its capitalization as soon as possible.
